Introduction

Se Se Se (Korean: 쎄쎄쎄) was a three-member girl group under Hee Record. They debuted on May 1, 1995, with their debut album "Se Se Se". They disbanded in 1997 due to difficult circumstances in their company.

Member Lee Yoonjeong withdrew from the group in 1996 due to issues with the agency while the remaining members in 1997, Jang Yujeong and Lim Eunsook transferred to a new agency continuing Se Se Se. Although a new member, Lee Hyunji, was recruited by the agency to release their third studio album, however the album was ultimately scrapped and thus they officially disbanded.

On January 28th, 2018 through an episode of The JTBC Toyu Project - Sugar Man 2 broadcast it was revealed that member Lim Eunsook has been battling with stage 4 breast cancer and she reported that she was recuperating in her hometown, Hongseong-gun, Chungcheongnam. On April 2018 she was shown being treated with chemotherapy in EBS's 'Medical Documentary Day 7'. Sadly on June 4th 2018, it was reported that Lim Eunsook had passed away at 44 years old in Seongnam-si, Gyeonggi-do, South Korea.
